###Block: Combat Traits
# Ability Name	Unique Key				Category of Ability		Type						Multiple Requirements																								Description																																															Source Page
Hill Fighter	KEY:Trait ~ Hill Fighter	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Hill Fighter],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait]	DESC:You are used to fighting in hilly environments. You may run or charge downhill on a steep slope (moving up to your base speed) without making an Acrobatics check to avoid stumbling - but if you travel farther than this distance, the normal rules for steep slopes apply.			SOURCEPAGE:p.23
Jungle Fighter	KEY:Trait ~ Jungle Fighter	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Jungle Fighter],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait]	DESC:You are sure-footed in jungle environments, and your speed may not be reduced to less than 10 feet by difficult terrain in jungles (meaning you may take a 5-foot step in difficult terrain and not provoke an attack of opportunity).									SOURCEPAGE:p.23
River Fighter	KEY:Trait ~ River Fighter	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,River Fighter],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait]	DESC:You are used to fighting while swimming. You may swim downstream or cross-current as a charge if you make your Swim DC by 5 or more.																										SOURCEPAGE:p.23
Savanna Hunter	KEY:Trait ~ Savanna Hunter	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Savanna Hunter],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait]	DESC:You have been trained to hunt and fight on the open plains since birth. You gain a +1 trait bonus on attacks of opportunity attack rolls made with a shortspear, as well as a +1 racial bonus on Constitution checks to continue running and avoid nonlethal damage from a forced march.	SOURCEPAGE:p.23

